past participle of 1go
adjective
not used before a noun
not present :no longer at a place

no longer existing
The days of the horse and buggy are (long) gone.
no longer living
There was nothing we could dohe was already gone. [=dead]
baseball :hit over the fence for a home run
The outfielder went back to the fence and jumped, but the ball was gone.
Brit informal :pregnant - used after a noun phrase indicating a length of time
She's six months gone. [=she became pregnant six months ago]
dead and gone
xem dead
far gone
xem far
gone on
informal + old-fashioned :feeling strong or foolish love for (someone)
Those two are really gone on each other.
preposition
Brit informal :after, past
It was (just) gone six when he got back.
